Build Directory for the seq66 library
Chris Ahlstrom
2026-04-23 to 2026-05-18

This directory is where all build products will reside.  See the following
document:

    cxx-pflR1
    The Pitchfork Layout (PFL)
    A Collection of Interesting Ideas, 2022-06-04

    https://api.csswg.org/bikeshed/?force=1&url=
        https://raw.githubusercontent.com/vector-of-bool/
            pitchfork/develop/data/spec.bs

    https://github.com/vector-of-bool/pitchfork

Note that we prefer to employ "3.1.2 Separate Header Placement".

Building the library:

    If the build directory contains only this README file, then run one of
    the following command sets in the top-level project directory:

    A.  $ ./work.sh             # options are available, use --help
    B.  $ meson . build
        $ cd build/cc
        $ ninja &> make.log

    If this directory is already populated, the following is an option:

    $ meson --reconfigure . build

    The default build directory is 'build/cc'. Some options change it
    to one of the following:

        build/clang
        build/cross (does not work at present)
        build/gcc
        build/portmidi
        build/rtmidi
        build/windows
        build/??? (see the --build option)

